1
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,600
SUSAN: And that's the news.

2
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:13,600
But before we sign off, we'd like
to congratulate our very own Evan Baxter,

3
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:17,500
who has just been elected
Buffalo's representative to Congress.

4
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:18,900
And, now, we have a surprise for Evan.

5
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,600
No, you don't.
We do.

6
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,500
Oh, no. I really didn't expect this.

7
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,800
Here's a look back at his run for office.

8
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,600
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

9
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,600
What are we gonna do?

10
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:31,100
ALL: Change the world!

11
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,200
That's right!

12
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,400
(ALL CHEERING)

13
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,500
ALL: Baxter! Baxter! Baxter!

14
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,500
Hi.

15
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,000
ALL: Baxter! Baxter!

16
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,500
That's right!

17
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:55,700
(CLEARING THROAT)

18
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:01,200
I feel like that old Indian
in front of all the garbage.

19
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:07,700
So, for the last time, this is Evan Baxter
for Eyewitness News. Good night.

20
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,000
(HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE RAIN PLAYING)

21
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:27,500
GPS: Huntsville, Virginia.
Prestige Crest, four miles.

22
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,100
What did we do before GPS?

23
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,200
Nothing.

24
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,500
Guys, Dad's very proud of his new car.

25
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:37,200
Hey, I am proud of my new car.
Look, I'm a politician now.

26
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,100
I'm in the public eye, and as you know,
when you are in the public eye,

27
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,900
image is everything, isn't it?

28
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,800
EVAN: Here it is! Welcome to the good life.

29
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:53,200
Hey, guys, why the long faces?
We're off on a new adventure!

30
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,400
It's just we're going to miss our friends.

31
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,300
You'll make new friends, better friends.

32
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,500
Yeah, richer friends.

33
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:03,400
Do not mouth off to me, sir.
I am the boss of you.

34
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:06,100
And let me tell you something,
you guys are gonna love this place.

35
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:09,800
And you know what? I think there's
something for our fishermen up there.

36
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,100
EVAN: Baxter family,
this is what's called a scenic vista.

37
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:18,000
And I don't think the big man himself
could do a better job. Pretty cool, huh?

38
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:19,900
Hey, Dad, an iguana can stay underwater
for 28 minutes.

39
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
What's that?

40
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:22,900
And a shrimp's heart is in its head.
Really?

41
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,200
Okay, someone's had enough Animal Planet
for one lifetime.

42
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,200
Yeah, let's head out! Come on.
The best is yet to come!

43
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,700
EVAN: Gentlemen, I have saved
the best for last.

44
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:35,300
Look over to the right.
That is your new home.

45
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,600
RYAN: Whoa!

46
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:43,900
JORDAN: That's our house?

47
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Uh-huh.
JOAN: I don't remember it being
this big in the brochure.

48
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,400
Was it this big in the brochure?

49
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:48,700
EVAN: Pretty amazing, isn't it?

50
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,400
There they are!

51
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,000
Is this curb appeal or what?

52
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,600
Here we go!

53
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:57,200
Honey, I think you're blocking my photo.

54
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,300
Sorry.

55
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,400
All right, everybody! Say "escrow"!

56
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,300
ALL: Escrow!

57
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,200
RYAN: Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Go. Go. Go.

58
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,700
EVAN: Guys, easy.

59
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,600
(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

60
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,300
This is our house?

61
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,400
Uh-huh.

62
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:15,500
MAN: Careful!

63
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,400
JOAN: Honey, be careful!
EVAN: Watch it!

64
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:18,600
Are you kidding me?

65
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:19,900
Mom, can we go upstairs?
JOAN: Yep.

66
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,400
And I get my own room, right?
Yep.

67
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,900
(YELLING EXCITEDLY)

68
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:25,500
Mr. Baxter, could you give us some
direction on these kitchen cabinets?

69
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,600
Sure.

70
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:31,200
Okay, it's between your maple
and your old-growth Brazilian cherry.

71
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:33,200
That is nice! Which is best?

72
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:36,300
Well, if you're not sensitive
to that "save the rainforest" stuff,

73
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,800
you can't beat the Brazilian cherry.

74
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,100
It's 200, 300 years old.

75
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,700
Three hundred years.
Three hundred.

76
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,300
Wow. That is old.

77
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,600
And now you are going to hold my dishes.

78
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,400
That's right. You going with the cherry?
Cheery cherry!

79
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,000
Yeah. Definitely.
He's going with the cherry!

80
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,300
RYAN: Dad, look!

81
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,700
No, no, no!

82
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,200
Ryan, do not touch him, please!

83
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,800
Oh, no, no, no, no, get him away!

84
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,200
No. He might have lice, fleas,
maggots or something.

85
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:01,000
You do not play with stray dogs
because they are very...

86
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,400
No, no! Get away, get away! Go!

87
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:05,600
Okay. Oh, no, no, no.

88
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,100
He's thirsty.
No, no, no.

89
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,100
No, you don't! There we go.

90
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,800
Well, Ryan, he's a stray.

91
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,300
If we give him water,
he's just going to come back.

92
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,900
Come on, Dad, why can't we keep him?
I mean, we've got a new house.

93
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,900
Okay, Ryan, this is why we can't keep him.

94
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,600
They are stinky. They are smelly.
They get hair all over the place.

95
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:22,900
They get a little thing called the mange.

96
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
In a nutshell, he is disgusting.
Case in point.

97
00:05:26,500 --> 00:05:28,400
(BOTH GIGGLING)

98
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:34,200
EVAN: Ladies and gentlemen,
this concludes day one

99
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,800
of the Baxters' new and exciting life.

100
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:38,200
I have to do the new house dance.

101
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:40,800
Wow! That dance?

102
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,400
Mmm-hmm.
That's a good new house dance.

103
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,800
Thank you.

104
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,000
You know, those boys were having
so much fun tonight,

105
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,100
I thought I would never get them to bed.

106
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:52,800
And then Ryan did the cutest thing.
He asked if we could all pray together.

107
00:05:53,300 --> 00:05:55,900
Really? What did you pray about?

108
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:58,000
He met a dog. What do you think
he prayed for?

109
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,000
(EXCLAIMING IN DISGUST)

110
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,800
Just a walking petri dish, that dog.

111
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:05,100
And Jordan was very precise.

112
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:08,900
He prayed for good visibility, good weather
on the hiking trip tomorrow.

113
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,300
The hiking trip? Oh, right. Yeah.
The hiking trip. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

114
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,300
You wanna know what I prayed for?

115
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:16,200
Yeah. What did you pray for?

116
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:19,400
I prayed we would become closer
as a family.

117
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:25,100
Honey, you don't need to pray for that
to happen. I will make that happen.

118
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:26,100
(SIGHING)

119
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,300
What would you pray for?

120
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:30,900
Me? I don't know. Praying just...

121
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,700
(SIGHING)

122
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:36,600
Honey, you're the one who said
you wanted to change the world.

123
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:39,000
It's a pretty big job.

124
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,600
If it were me,
I would take all the help I could get.

125
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:47,100
(CROWD CHEERING)

126
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:50,300
WOMAN OVER TV: Former Buffalo News
anchor, Evan Baxter, takes office tomorrow

127
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,700
to make good on a lofty campaign promise.

128
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,900
What are we going to do?

129
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,300
ALL: Change the world!

130
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:58,800
WOMAN OVER TV: Good luck, Congressman.
Many have tried, many have failed.

131
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,100
Hello!

132
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:02,000
This is Regina Sparks reporting for...

133
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,900
(SIGHING)

134
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,400
(CLEARING THROAT)

135
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,300
Hello, there. Hi.

136
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,700
This is Evan Baxter.

137
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,800
Just wanted to say thank you for everything.

138
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:32,700
Thank you for the new car and for the house.

139
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:35,700
The house is great. I love it.

140
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:41,100
I mean, I picked it out,
but you created matter and everything, so...

141
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:48,100
I just wanted to say that I think
Joan makes a good point,

142
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:52,700
and that I am now in a position
of great power,

143
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:56,600
and I know that with great power
comes great responsibility.

144
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,900
So, God,

145
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,000
(CLEARING THROAT)

146
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,200
Please help me change the world.

147
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:12,000
Okay. That's it. I'm hanging up now.

148
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:15,400
God bless... Well, you. Okay.

149
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,400
(ALARM RINGING)

150
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,500
What? That's weird.

151
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,600
What?

152
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,300
I set the alarm for 7:00.

153
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:47,800
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

154
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,000
(GRUNTING)

155
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,300
(SNEEZING)

156
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,000
(GRUNTING)

157
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,500
I am successful. I am powerful.
I am handsome.

158
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,200
I am happy, successful,
powerful, handsome, happy.

159
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:28,600
All right, everyone, wish me luck.
The Congressman has left the building.

160
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:33,500
All right, Baxter brood, I will see you
later on this afternoon for the big hike. Yes?

161
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,800
EVAN: You psyched? Are you ready?

162
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:35,900
ALL: Yeah.

163
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,200
Bye. See you.
Good luck, honey.

164
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,500
Bye, guys!
See you later.

165
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,500
Later, gator.

166
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,500
(EXCLAIMING)

167
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,900
Oh, gosh.

168
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:45,700
Wow. Honey, did you order anything?

169
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,200
"Alpha and Omega Hardware"?

170
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,200
JOAN: Never heard of them.

171
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,500
Me either.

172
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,900
What do we have?

173
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,300
(GASPING)

174
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,800
What is this stuff?

175
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,000
Must have the wrong address.

176
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,700
Yup. The wrong address.

177
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,500
WOMAN: Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.
Good morning.

178
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,000
MAN 1: Good morning,
Congressman Baxter.
Hello.

179
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,500
MAN 2: Good morning,
Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.

180
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,600
Oh, this is so cool.

181
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,700
Uh-huh.

182
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,600
Yeah. This'll work.

183
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:22,600
There he is! The head honcho.
The big kahuna.

184
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:24,600
Rita, I think I have to do the dance.

185
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:25,900
Do the dance.

186
00:10:25,900 --> 00:10:27,300
(GRUNTING)

187
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,800
That's enough of the dance.

188
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,000
Oh, this is nice! This is really nice!

189
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:35,700
This is too nice.
There's something crooked going on.

190
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,000
Do you smell anthrax?

191
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:39,000
Congressman!
Hey, Marty!

192
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,500
Nice sound to that.
I like it.

193
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,500
Here they are!

194
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,600
(ALL CHEERING)

195
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:43,800
All right.

196
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,600
You remember Sarah, Allen, Michael.

197
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:48,400
I don't think you know the new kid
Eugene Tennanbaum. I found him at G.W.

198
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,600
Sort of a walking search engine. Watch this.
How many stars on the flag in 1818?

199
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:52,700
15.

200
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:54,700
And Congressman Baxter's coffee habits?

201
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:57,800
He likes a morning latte with a cruller,
a decaf espresso after lunch,

202
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,500
served sans pastry of any kind.

203
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:02,200
Very impressive. A little freaky,
but I like this kid.

204
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,900
(LAUGHING) I love you.

205
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:05,900
Hmm?

206
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:09,900
I mean, we should hang out socially.
I just got a ping-pong table.

207
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,500
Not going to happen.

208
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:14,800
Go find out where his license plates are.
Everybody else, back to your holes.

209
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:15,900
EUGENE: He was actually right.

210
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,800
I'm doing a background check on that kid.

211
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:22,600
Ta-da! This, my friend, is a power office,
to remind you of the mission!

212
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,100
BOTH: "Change the world!"

213
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,900
Okay, Evan, who do you know?
What do you mean?

214
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,900
Oh, come on.
Yesterday we're in the basement.

215
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,800
Today, look at this place.
It's like the Emerald City!

216
00:11:29,900 --> 00:11:33,200
"Enjoy your office.
Your neighbor, Congressman Long."

217
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:35,500
Congressman Long did this?
Did you say "neighbor"?

218
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,400
That's right. He lives in Prestige Crest,
right up the street.

219
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:42,300
Evan, you got to tell me these things.
Think of the publicity angle on this!

220
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,800
You and Congressman Long
having a barbecue.

221
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:46,800
Congressman Long eating your hot dog.

222
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,500
RITA: Hate to break up
your little weenie roast.

223
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:51,300
Congressman Long's assistant
just dropped this off.

224
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,700
The Congressman would like for you

225
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,000
to junior cosponsor this bill
that he's introducing.

226
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:59,400
Hold on. Congressman Long asked us to
junior cosponsor his bill? What's the bill?

227
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:02,100
The Citizens' Integration of Public Lands Act.

228
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:05,400
Never heard of it. Gene, here, now.
Rita, why didn't you tell me about this?

229
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,600
I just did.

230
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,300
You need to tell me about it
before I need to know about it.

231
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,500
Marty, you are not the vice congressman.
I am the legislative...

232
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:14,400
Nobody voted for you. If Evan gets shot
in the head, you do not automatically...

233
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,400
If Evan got shot in the head,
you're the first suspect.

234
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,500
Play nice. Play nice.

235
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,600
All right, Eugene, Congressman Long's bill.
What is it?

236
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:22,700
HR7124, better known as CINPLAN.

237
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:25,500
The bill would open up fringe areas
of the national parks for development.

238
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,900
Long's been sitting on it for ages...

239
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,100
Got it. Pause. Come on, Evan, this is huge.

240
00:12:29,100 --> 00:12:30,600
You hitch your wagon to the right star,

241
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,900
you could ride all the way down
to Pennsylvania Avenue.

242
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,300
This is day one.

243
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,600
You got your name on a major piece
of legislation!

244
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,600
Oh, and another thing,
he wants you to read it today.

245
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,300
Well, I can't do it today.

246
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,500
I promised my kids...
Eugene.

247
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,500
