00:54:15,600 --> 00:54:17,500
I'm afraid I can't do that, sir.

998
00:54:17,600 --> 00:54:19,000
Congressman!

999
00:54:19,100 --> 00:54:21,300
These animals are not trained.

1000
00:54:21,400 --> 00:54:22,700
Congressman!

1001
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:25,100
I think they want me to save them!

1002
00:54:25,100 --> 00:54:27,700
Save them from what, Congressman?

1003
00:54:27,900 --> 00:54:31,200
Saving the animals, okay.
I can roll with that. That's a good idea.

1004
00:54:39,000 --> 00:54:40,000
The flood.

1005
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:42,900
A flood? Rolling out.

1006
00:54:43,400 --> 00:54:44,700
CONGRESSPERSON: The flood.

1007
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:46,900
This has been the hottest,
driest summer on record

1008
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:48,700
and you say we're going to have a flood?

1009
00:54:48,700 --> 00:54:50,000
When might we expect this?

1010
00:54:50,100 --> 00:54:52,200
September 22, midday.

1011
00:54:52,300 --> 00:54:53,300
(CROWD CHATTERING)

1012
00:54:56,100 --> 00:54:57,600
That's what I was told.

1013
00:54:57,700 --> 00:54:59,700
Might I ask who told you?

1014
00:55:06,600 --> 00:55:10,400
Not in front of all those people.
Don't say it. Don't say it.

1015
00:55:15,500 --> 00:55:16,800
God.

1016
00:55:17,500 --> 00:55:18,500
(SOBBING)

1017
00:55:21,600 --> 00:55:24,400
God? You talk to God?

1018
00:55:25,100 --> 00:55:26,300
Yes.

1019
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:27,600
LONG: And God is talking back?

1020
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:31,400
Yeah. We hung out a little.

1021
00:55:31,500 --> 00:55:33,800
Well, time to update the resume.

1022
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:36,200
Congressman, your name is being
removed from this bill.

1023
00:55:36,300 --> 00:55:39,800
Obviously, the stresses of this office
have proven too much for you.

1024
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,200
Please have the congressman removed.

1025
00:55:41,300 --> 00:55:43,100
No. Please! You don't understand!

1026
00:55:43,200 --> 00:55:46,000
God commanded me to build an ark!

1027
00:55:46,100 --> 00:55:48,700
It's going to rain!
There's going to be a flood!

1028
00:55:50,100 --> 00:55:51,600
Remove him now!

1029
00:55:51,700 --> 00:55:54,100
We have to prepare ourselves!

1030
00:55:54,200 --> 00:55:56,900
I need to finish the ark!

1031
00:55:56,900 --> 00:55:58,000
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

1032
00:55:58,100 --> 00:55:59,700
Remove him now!

1033
00:56:06,700 --> 00:56:08,600
Does this mean we're moving back home?

1034
00:56:09,600 --> 00:56:12,300
Home, Canada. One or the other.

1035
00:56:22,800 --> 00:56:27,700
Joan? I know you probably saw
what happened, but I can explain.

1036
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:34,600
Take the stuff to the car, guys.
I'll be there in a minute.

1037
00:56:37,600 --> 00:56:38,700
Guys?

1038
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:41,400
(DOOR OPENING)

1039
00:56:42,300 --> 00:56:47,400
I'm gonna take them to my mother's.
Evan, I think you need help.

1040
00:56:48,000 --> 00:56:52,800
Joan, please. I'm not doing this.
It's not me. It's him.

1041
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:56,200
I went to that meeting in a suit,
and he took it off of me.

1042
00:56:56,200 --> 00:57:00,000
Those animals are following me
because of him.

1043
00:57:00,100 --> 00:57:03,700
God? Does God know
he's destroying our lives?

1044
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:06,300
Does God know he's going to get you fired?

1045
00:57:06,400 --> 00:57:08,200
Yeah! He's trying to get me fired!

1046
00:57:09,000 --> 00:57:12,100
He is trying to get me fired!

1047
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:14,400
That way I'll have more time
to work on the ark!

1048
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:16,900
Because the rain and the floods are coming.

1049
00:57:17,000 --> 00:57:20,500
No, I heard you, Evan.
The whole world heard you.

1050
00:57:20,500 --> 00:57:23,200
Joan, please, you gotta believe me.

1051
00:57:23,300 --> 00:57:24,400
(DRIZZLING)

1052
00:57:25,600 --> 00:57:30,400
There it is! It's happening!
It's happening! It's raining!

1053
00:57:47,900 --> 00:57:49,100
Goodbye, Evan.

1054
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:52,000
(ENGINE STARTING)

1055
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:53,900
Joan!

1056
00:58:02,700 --> 00:58:07,200
I know! I know. Whatever you do,
you do because you love me!

1057
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:17,800
Do me a favor. Love me less.

1058
00:58:19,200 --> 00:58:20,300
REPORTER: Congressman!

1059
00:58:20,300 --> 00:58:23,300
WOMAN: Are you concerned at all
about Congressman Baxter's tirade

1060
00:58:23,400 --> 00:58:25,000
and the adverse effects
it may have on your bill?

1061
00:58:25,100 --> 00:58:28,900
The day it rains and floods and
Congressman Baxter takes a ride on his ark,

1062
00:58:29,000 --> 00:58:31,000
that'll be the day
I'll be concerned. Thank you.

1063
00:58:31,100 --> 00:58:33,500
(WAITING ON THE WORLD
TO CHANGE PLAYING)

1064
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:36,000
(BLEATING)

1065
00:58:36,100 --> 00:58:40,400
His name is Evan Baxter,
but now he goes by "New York's Noah,"

1066
00:58:40,500 --> 00:58:44,200
"Heaven's Evan,"
"The Weirdo with a Beardo."

1067
00:58:49,100 --> 00:58:52,800
Okay, guys. Watch it. Watch it.
Coming through. Watch your back.

1068
00:58:54,400 --> 00:58:58,100
Marty, will you comment on Congressman
Baxter's change of appearance?

1069
00:58:58,400 --> 00:59:02,300
Yes, his hair is long.
Yes, his beard is unshaven.

1070
00:59:02,400 --> 00:59:04,600
Are you equally stunned
by this man's appearance?

1071
00:59:11,000 --> 00:59:12,200
The way things go around here,

1072
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:15,000
if he gets any crazier,
we may end up in the White House.

1073
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:20,900
(REPORTER SPEAKING SPANISH)

1074
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:24,000
Hey! No, no, no! That's my cup!

1075
00:59:25,600 --> 00:59:26,900
Whatever.

1076
00:59:47,700 --> 00:59:51,200
He's filling the boat with
two of every kind of animal.

1077
00:59:51,300 --> 00:59:54,700
Still to be collected,
two giraffes, two elephants

1078
00:59:55,700 --> 00:59:57,300
and one more jackass.

1079
01:00:00,600 --> 01:00:01,700
What an idiot.

1080
01:00:01,700 --> 01:00:03,200
He's a mook.

1081
01:00:03,300 --> 01:00:04,500
Jerks.

1082
01:00:05,500 --> 01:00:08,100
Don't worry about it, you guys.
Come on, eat up.

1083
01:00:08,200 --> 01:00:09,200
Not hungry.

1084
01:00:09,300 --> 01:00:10,400
Yeah, me neither.

1085
01:00:10,500 --> 01:00:12,800
You guys can't eat. I can't stop.

1086
01:00:12,900 --> 01:00:14,800
Can I go to the bathroom?
Me, too?

1087
01:00:14,900 --> 01:00:17,500
Okay. Dylan, go with them. Please?

1088
01:00:17,600 --> 01:00:18,800
Fine.

1089
01:00:21,500 --> 01:00:23,500
Excuse me. Can I get a refill, please?

1090
01:00:24,200 --> 01:00:25,300
Coming right up.

1091
01:00:26,200 --> 01:00:27,200
Thank you.

1092
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:29,000
Excuse me. Are you all right?

1093
01:00:29,900 --> 01:00:30,900
Yeah.

1094
01:00:32,700 --> 01:00:35,000
No. It's a long story.

1095
01:00:35,100 --> 01:00:36,200
Well, I like stories.

1096
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:40,000
I'm considered a bit of a storyteller myself.

1097
01:00:41,100 --> 01:00:43,700
My husband...
Have you heard of "New York's Noah"?

1098
01:00:45,800 --> 01:00:47,500
The guy who's building the ark.

1099
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:48,900
That's him.

1100
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:52,100
I love that story, Noah and the Ark.

1101
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:53,800
You know, a lot of people miss
the point of that story.

1102
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:55,900
They think it's about God's wrath and anger.

1103
01:00:56,800 --> 01:00:58,600
They love it when God gets angry.

1104
01:00:58,600 --> 01:01:01,100
What is the story about, then? The ark?

1105
01:01:01,200 --> 01:01:06,600
Well, I think it's a love story
about believing in each other.

1106
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:12,300
You know, the animals showed up in pairs.
They stood by each other, side by side,

1107
01:01:12,400 --> 01:01:16,700
just like Noah and his family.
Everybody entered the ark side by side.

1108
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:20,700
But my husband says God told him to do it.

1109
01:01:22,500 --> 01:01:24,100
What do you do with that?

1110
01:01:24,200 --> 01:01:26,000
Sounds like an opportunity.

1111
01:01:29,000 --> 01:01:30,300
Let me ask you something.

1112
01:01:31,300 --> 01:01:34,500
If someone prays for patience,
you think God gives them patience?

1113
01:01:35,100 --> 01:01:38,400
Or does he give them
the opportunity to be patient?

1114
01:01:40,100 --> 01:01:42,200
If they pray for courage,
does God give them courage,

1115
01:01:42,200 --> 01:01:44,900
or does he give them opportunities
to be courageous?

1116
01:01:47,100 --> 01:01:49,500
If someone prayed
for their family to be closer,

1117
01:01:50,700 --> 01:01:53,600
you think God zaps them
with warm, fuzzy feelings?

1118
01:01:54,500 --> 01:01:56,900
Or does he give them opportunities
to love each other?

1119
01:01:58,800 --> 01:02:00,000
(GASPS QUIETLY)

1120
01:02:00,100 --> 01:02:04,200
Well, I got to run.
A lot of people to serve. Enjoy.

1121
01:02:11,200 --> 01:02:14,200
JON: Guess this comes as no surprise to
those who remember his campaign promise,

1122
01:02:14,300 --> 01:02:16,100
"I will lower taxes,

1123
01:02:16,500 --> 01:02:18,700
"go crazy and build a gigantic ark."

1124
01:02:18,800 --> 01:02:19,600
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1125
01:02:26,800 --> 01:02:28,800
JOAN: Oh, my gosh.

1126
01:02:33,400 --> 01:02:34,400
JOAN: Evan!

1127
01:02:34,500 --> 01:02:35,600
Dad?

1128
01:02:35,700 --> 01:02:36,800
Honey!

1129
01:02:36,900 --> 01:02:37,900
Dad?

1130
01:02:37,900 --> 01:02:39,700
You guys, I'm up here.

1131
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:56,400
(LAUGHING)

1132
01:02:56,900 --> 01:02:58,900
Rough week?
JORDAN: You look really funny.

1133
01:02:59,000 --> 01:03:00,200
You look really old.

1134
01:03:00,300 --> 01:03:01,800
Yeah, well, he is really old.

1135
01:03:04,000 --> 01:03:05,200
Why'd you come back?

1136
01:03:05,300 --> 01:03:06,400
It was the kids.

1137
01:03:06,500 --> 01:03:07,600
Tell him, guys.

1138
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:09,700
We like you better as the crazy guy.

1139
01:03:09,700 --> 01:03:12,100
You spend time with us
and you're home a lot more.

1140
01:03:12,200 --> 01:03:14,800
Just, please don't make us do
the dance anymore.

1141
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:33,200
(SIGHING)

1142
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:40,900
I don't know what's going on,
or what you're going through,

1143
01:03:41,600 --> 01:03:43,400
but we got into this as a family

1144
01:03:44,600 --> 01:03:47,300
and we're gonna get out of it as a family,

1145
01:03:48,200 --> 01:03:49,800
side by side.

1146
01:03:57,300 --> 01:04:00,700
But, Evan, we have to talk about the ark.
It has to come down.

1147
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:02,100
I can't do that.

1148
01:04:02,200 --> 01:04:03,600
You don't have a choice.

1149
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:07,600
JOAN: Congressman Long went to the city.
There's a laundry list of code violations.

1150
01:04:07,600 --> 01:04:10,100
You have until September 22
to take it down,

1151
01:04:10,100 --> 01:04:12,000
or they'll take it down and arrest you.

1152
01:04:12,100 --> 01:04:14,100
September 22. That's the day of the flood.

1153
01:04:14,200 --> 01:04:15,700
Mom! Dad! Come here!

1154
01:04:22,000 --> 01:04:24,300
(ANIMALS CALLING)

1155
01:04:40,800 --> 01:04:43,200
Don't you dare take that ark down.

1156
01:04:45,800 --> 01:04:47,700
How are we gonna do this?

1157
01:04:47,800 --> 01:04:50,000
There's no way the five
of us can finish on time.

1158
01:04:50,100 --> 01:04:52,200
We don't have money to hire anybody else.

1159
01:04:52,200 --> 01:04:53,500
(ALPACA CRYING)

1160
01:04:57,300 --> 01:04:59,200
Is that a llama with a hammer?

1161
01:04:59,300 --> 01:05:02,800
An alpaca. They rarely spit at people
unless frightened or abused.

1162
01:05:05,300 --> 01:05:06,500
Let's finish this sucker.

1163
01:05:08,600 --> 01:05:09,600
(READY FOR A MIRACLE PLAYING)

1164
01:05:10,700 --> 01:05:11,700
(ELEPHANT TRUMPETING)

1165
01:05:11,800 --> 01:05:13,000
Come on, let's go.

1166
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,400
WOMAN: No one knows
where they came from

1167
01:05:14,500 --> 01:05:16,300
or how the congressman
is getting them to do it,

1168
01:05:16,400 --> 01:05:22,300
but, two by two, animals of all kinds
are working with Godspeed to build this ark.

1169
01:05:22,400 --> 01:05:23,900
Thank you.

1170
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:27,200
If this flood really does happen,
"Evan help us."

1171
01:05:28,800 --> 01:05:30,300
Hey! A little help?

1172
01:05:34,300 --> 01:05:35,300
Thanks.

1173
01:05:36,700 --> 01:05:37,800
JOAN: Here it is, hon.

1174
01:05:38,100 --> 01:05:39,000
(MONKEY GIBBERING)

1175
01:05:39,100 --> 01:05:41,800
Perfect. Thanks.

1176
01:05:45,800 --> 01:05:47,300
Hold it right there.

1177
01:05:47,400 --> 01:05:51,000
This is Ed Carson coming to you
live from New York Noah's construction site,

1178
01:05:51,000 --> 01:05:56,100
where we are unable to leave the news van
due to hazardous conditions outside.

1179
01:05:59,300 --> 01:06:00,300
High five.
High five.

1180
01:06:00,300 --> 01:06:01,300
Good job.

1181
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:03,700
Hey, putty tat.

1182
01:06:06,000 --> 01:06:07,700
(SHRIEKING)

1183
01:06:07,700 --> 01:06:10,600
Go, go, go! He tried to eat me!

1184
01:06:10,900 --> 01:06:13,600
Dylan! Jordan! Check it out!
Your mom's building an ark!

1185
01:06:13,700 --> 01:06:15,000
Let's do the dance.

1186
01:06:15,100 --> 01:06:17,100
JOAN: No, please, no.

1187
01:06:18,700 --> 01:06:19,700
(HONKING)

1188
01:06:19,800 --> 01:06:21,700
WOMAN 1: Well, where did
the animals come from, then?

1189
01:06:21,800 --> 01:06:22,900
WOMAN 2: Please. It's a trick.

1190
01:06:23,000 --> 01:06:24,400
WOMAN 3: It's a circus is what it is.

1191
01:06:24,500 --> 01:06:27,600
Wild animals running amok
in suburban Virginia.

1192
01:06:27,600 --> 01:06:31,300
With all these species,
what's being done about the feces?

1193
01:06:37,400 --> 01:06:42,700
Evan Baxter! You have gone from newsman
to congressman to caveman.

1194
01:06:42,800 --> 01:06:45,300
What makes you so sure God chose you?

1195
01:06:46,600 --> 01:06:48,300
He chose all of us.

1196
01:06:57,700 --> 01:06:59,600
Time to wash up, you guys.

1197
01:07:06,200 --> 01:07:07,400
Thanks.

1198
01:07:10,800 --> 01:07:12,300
You want some?

1199
01:07:32,600 --> 01:07:35,700
RITA: Why couldn't the man
just buy a Corvette?

1200
01:07:35,800 --> 01:07:40,000
Well, well, well. There they are.
It is good to see you guys.

1201
01:07:40,100 --> 01:07:45,100
It's good to see you! Your hair looks great.
It's very regal. Man, I love your hair!

1202
01:07:45,200 --> 01:07:46,600
And you're still sucking up.

1203
01:07:46,700 --> 01:07:47,700
So, why are you here?

1204
01:07:47,800 --> 01:07:48,900
Long locked us out.

1205
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:50,000
He can't do that.

1206
01:07:50,100 --> 01:07:52,300
I mean, I've been suspended,
but I'm still a congressman.

1207
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:53,500
Rita, tell him what you know.

1208
01:07:53,600 --> 01:07:54,600
Tell me what?

1209
01:07:54,700 --> 01:07:57,500
I smelled a rat the second we got that office.

1210
01:07:57,600 --> 01:07:59,600
You don't get an office
like that for nothing.

1211
01:07:59,700 --> 01:08:02,900
So I had the stalker here do some research.

1212
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:04,100
Okay, Eugene, talk.

1213
01:08:04,500 --> 01:08:06,300
Prestige Crest used to be federal lands,

1214
01:08:06,400 --> 01:08:09,300
but what's interesting is
how it got into private hands.

1215
01:08:09,300 --> 01:08:11,700
Congressman Long got the approval
to build a dam

1216
01:08:11,800 --> 01:08:14,700
and then passed out the surrounding lands
to a group of private investors.

1217
01:08:14,800 --> 01:08:16,100
Now, the locals fought this thing for years.

1218
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:18,400
They said Long and his developer buddies
were cutting corners,

1219
01:08:18,500 --> 01:08:20,800
like skipping important
building code checkpoints.

1220
01:08:20,800 --> 01:08:23,900
And with the land use bill, he's gonna do
the same thing with the national parks.

1221
01:08:24,000 --> 01:08:27,700
So, you stand by and shake your pom-poms
while Long and his buddies get rich.

1222
01:08:27,800 --> 01:08:29,900
What can we do? I'm suspended.

1223
01:08:30,000 --> 01:08:33,400
Go back to the Hill and show them
that you can and will fight this bill.

1224
01:08:33,500 --> 01:08:36,500
You guys, I'm sorry. I can't do that.
I have to get back to the ark.

1225
01:08:36,500 --> 01:08:38,200
The ark? All right. Okay.

1226
01:08:38,300 --> 01:08:40,200
God told you to build an ark?
Yes.

1227
01:08:40,300 --> 01:08:43,300
But did he tell you to make your friends
believe in you and follow you here

1228
01:08:43,400 --> 01:08:46,500
so you can make us look stupid?
'Cause I go to church every Sunday.

1229
01:08:47,700 --> 01:08:49,000
Okay, every other Sunday.

1230
01:08:50,000 --> 01:08:53,500
I've been to church!
And that does not sound like God to me.

1231
01:08:53,600 --> 01:08:56,000
Rita, I know that this
doesn't make any sense.

1232
01:08:56,000 --> 01:08:58,700
I just want you to trust me.
You just have to have faith.

1233
01:08:58,800 --> 01:09:03,400
Evan, faith will not fight this bill.
The CINPLAN vote is today!

1234
01:09:03,500 --> 01:09:07,300
If we're going to stop this thing,
you need to get down to Capitol Hill now!

1235
01:09:07,300 --> 01:09:08,700
Otherwise, it's impossible!

1236
01:09:08,800 --> 01:09:11,600
Dad, Dad, I think it's done.

1237
01:10:10,200 --> 01:10:14,400
What in the world?
I can't even get my cat to use the litter box.

1238
01:10:55,800 --> 01:11:00,300
It's September 22, and we're all still here.

1239
01:11:00,300 --> 01:11:01,600
Awkward!

1240
01:11:01,900 --> 01:11:05,300
People! The flood is imminent!

1241
01:11:05,400 --> 01:11:09,000
Board the ark! Save yourselves!

1242
01:11:09,100 --> 01:11:10,500
MAN: Get down, you fool!

1243
01:11:11,000 --> 01:11:15,000
Listen to me! The time has come!

1244
01:11:15,100 --> 01:11:19,200
No, Captain Ahab! Your time has come!

1245
01:11:19,200 --> 01:11:20,400
(ALL LAUGHING)

1246
01:11:20,500 --> 01:11:25,200
Yeah, Baxter! The weather's 70 and sunny
with a chance of crazy!

1247
01:11:25,300 --> 01:11:26,700
(ALL GIGGLING)

1248
01:11:28,400 --> 01:11:30,500
(RUMBLING)

1249
01:11:30,600 --> 01:11:34,800
Do you hear that? The rains are upon us!

1250
01:11:34,900 --> 01:11:36,600
Dad, I don't think that's the rains.

1251
01:11:37,900 --> 01:11:39,100
(SIREN BLARING)

1252
01:11:41,000 --> 01:11:43,700
MAN: Hey, Baxter! Kiss your ark goodbye!

1253
01:11:56,100 --> 01:11:57,200
Where is he?

1254
01:11:57,200 --> 01:11:58,300
On the boat, sir.

1255
01:11:59,300 --> 01:12:01,400
Give me a minute.
Lets see if I can convince "Noah"

1256
01:12:01,500 --> 01:12:03,300
that the world doesn't have to end today.

1257
01:12:07,400 --> 01:12:10,400
I gotta hand it to you,
this is quite the show.

1258
01:12:10,500 --> 01:12:13,500
According to my source,
the show hasn't even started yet.

1259
01:12:13,600 --> 01:12:15,300
Still expecting the big flood.

1260
01:12:15,300 --> 01:12:17,600
You know, voters don't respond
to the gloom and doom stuff.

1261
01:12:17,700 --> 01:12:19,200
They like a more positive message.

1262
01:12:19,200 --> 01:12:20,800
Like the one you're sending with your bill?

1263
01:12:20,900 --> 01:12:22,900
How much did you make off of all this land?

1264
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:26,300
You are destroying
our national parks for profit.

1265
01:12:26,300 --> 01:12:28,200
You have a problem with somebody
taking a little profit?

1266
01:12:28,300 --> 01:12:29,800
It's called business, son.

1267
01:12:29,900 --> 01:12:32,400
So if I need to get a message out there,
or get a congressman elected

1268
01:12:32,500 --> 01:12:36,500
there are people who pay for it, and yes,
those people want this bill to happen

1269
01:12:36,600 --> 01:12:40,100
and, by God, it's gonna happen.
Now you look down there.

1270
01:12:41,200 --> 01:12:43,000
Those are the wolves, son.

1271
01:12:43,000 --> 01:12:46,200
I'm gonna give you one last chance.
Take down this boat.

1272
01:12:46,200 --> 01:12:50,000
I'm giving you one last chance. Repent.

1273
01:12:51,300 --> 01:12:55,200
Such a shame. You had possibilities.

1274
01:12:55,300 --> 01:12:59,100
But you want to stop progress
to save the Earth. Go for it.

1275
01:12:59,200 --> 01:13:01,400
Good luck getting a tree
to come to the polls.

1276
01:13:07,100 --> 01:13:08,600
Take it down.

1277
01:13:15,900 --> 01:13:19,100
This is a court order approving
the demolition of this boat!

1278
01:13:19,200 --> 01:13:22,200
Evacuate immediately!
You have three minutes!

1279
01:13:24,900 --> 01:13:29,100
Honey. We have to go.
They're going to destroy the boat.

1280
01:13:29,900 --> 01:13:31,000
No.

1281
01:13:32,100 --> 01:13:33,500
It can't end this way.

1282
01:13:35,300 --> 01:13:39,300
Is it too much to ask
for a little precipitation?

1283
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:44,200
Honey, maybe God didn't mean
a literal flood.

1284
01:13:44,300 --> 01:13:49,600
Maybe he meant a flood of knowledge
or emotion or awareness.

1285
01:13:49,700 --> 01:13:51,300
If that's true,

1286
01:13:52,200 --> 01:13:55,400
I am going to be so pissed.

1287
01:13:55,500 --> 01:13:56,800
Two minutes!

1288
01:13:56,800 --> 01:14:00,300
Get off the boat now
or you will be removed by force.

1289
01:14:00,400 --> 01:14:03,900
Evan, you did it. You built the ark.

1290
01:14:04,000 --> 01:14:05,400
That's all you were asked to do, right?

1291
01:14:05,400 --> 01:14:06,500
No.

1292
01:14:07,000 --> 01:14:11,200
There's something else.
Something's going to happen. I can feel it.

1293
01:14:11,300 --> 01:14:14,100
Yeah, what's gonna happen is
tear gas and a wrecking ball.

1294
01:14:14,200 --> 01:14:16,200
Evan, think of the kids.

1295
01:14:17,300 --> 01:14:18,700
One minute!

1296
01:14:20,900 --> 01:14:23,000
Dad, whatever you say, I'm with you.

1297
01:14:23,000 --> 01:14:24,500
Yeah, me, too.

1298
01:14:24,600 --> 01:14:26,700
Me, too. But can we keep
some of the animals?

1299
01:14:26,700 --> 01:14:29,000
I like the alpaca. He spits.

1300
01:14:33,500 --> 01:14:36,800
You're right. We did it. We built the boat.

1301
01:14:37,200 --> 01:14:38,200
Yeah.

1302
01:14:39,200 --> 01:14:41,600
Let's go. Let's go, guys. Come on.

1303
01:14:54,700 --> 01:14:56,400
EVAN: Well, I guess they don't want to go.

1304
01:14:56,500 --> 01:14:57,900
It's their instinct.

1305
01:14:58,000 --> 01:14:59,600
What do you mean, hon?

1306
01:14:59,700 --> 01:15:04,400
Some animals know when weather's coming.
When they feel it coming, they sit.

1307
01:15:10,300 --> 01:15:11,800
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1308
01:15:12,600 --> 01:15:13,700
Joan!

1309
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:18,400
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1310
01:15:23,100 --> 01:15:25,600
Okay. Time's up! We're coming in!

1311
01:15:25,700 --> 01:15:28,900
Get that ball in position!
We're clearing them out!

1312
01:15:35,700 --> 01:15:37,600
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1313
01:15:39,900 --> 01:15:43,200
Is that rain?
It's raining.

1314
01:15:43,200 --> 01:15:45,700
Lucky guess, Baxter. Lucky guess.

1315
01:15:47,300 --> 01:15:48,200
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1316
01:16:04,100 --> 01:16:06,500
Looks like the drought's finally over.
Good news, eh, Congressman?

1317
01:16:06,600 --> 01:16:08,800
Yeah. Good news.

1318
01:16:11,300 --> 01:16:16,800
Everybody! Please! Get on the ark!

1319
01:16:18,800 --> 01:16:20,300
Go to the car!

1320
01:16:20,400 --> 01:16:24,500
Please! Everyone! On the ark!

1321
01:16:24,600 --> 01:16:27,900
Cover me up! Keep me dry!
Cover me up! Keep me dry!

1322
01:16:28,000 --> 01:16:32,000
Who's crazy now, huh?
Look at us all squishing!

1323
01:16:40,100 --> 01:16:41,800
It kind of stopped raining.

1324
01:16:41,900 --> 01:16:43,000
Is that it?

1325
01:16:43,000 --> 01:16:45,500
What did I tell you? It's fine. It's over.

1326
01:16:45,600 --> 01:16:47,500
Hey, Ahab! This is it?

1327
01:16:48,300 --> 01:16:50,800
Your God experiencing
a little water shortage?

1328
01:16:50,900 --> 01:16:51,900
(ALL LAUGHING)

1329
01:16:52,000 --> 01:16:55,700
It would appear Evan Baxter
was right about the rain,

1330
01:16:55,700 --> 01:16:59,200
with a slight miscalculation
as to the quantity.

1331
01:17:03,300 --> 01:17:04,900
Something's wrong.

1332
01:17:04,900 --> 01:17:06,500
Honey, the clouds are moving away.

1333
01:17:06,600 --> 01:17:09,600
No, no. No, this isn't right.

1334
01:17:10,400 --> 01:17:13,800
Evan, even if it kept raining,
it's not like it could cause a flood in a day.

1335
01:17:13,900 --> 01:17:19,100
But today is the day! It has to be.
This just doesn't make any sense!

1336
01:17:21,100 --> 01:17:22,200
Wait a second.

1337
01:17:22,300 --> 01:17:23,300
What is it?

1338
01:17:23,400 --> 01:17:27,100
Marty said that Long cut corners,
violated building codes.

1339
01:17:27,200 --> 01:17:28,300
What are you talking about?

1340
01:17:28,400 --> 01:17:29,800
The lake, Long Lake.

1341
01:17:29,900 --> 01:17:33,500
It's named after him.
It's the lake! It's the lake!

1342
01:17:46,900 --> 01:17:48,200
Oh, no.

1343
01:17:50,000 --> 01:17:54,800
Get on the ark! Everyone, on the ark now!

1344
01:17:54,900 --> 01:17:56,700
I think we should get on the ark.

1345
01:17:56,800 --> 01:17:59,600
I agree. I think we should get on the ark also.

1346
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:02,700
I'm cold. I'm wet. I'm going home.

1347
01:18:10,300 --> 01:18:12,400
Ladies first! Move!

1348
01:18:20,300 --> 01:18:23,900
Oh, my God. This is happening.
This is really happening.

1349
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:28,400
Holy... Get everyone on the ark now!

1350
01:18:28,400 --> 01:18:31,100
Get on the ark now! Let's go!
Get on the ark! Let's go!

1351
01:18:31,200 --> 01:18:34,100
Go, go, go! Get on the ark!

1352
01:18:34,100 --> 01:18:35,600
(ALL SCREAMING)

1353
01:18:35,700 --> 01:18:39,800
Go, go, go! On the ark! Go, go, go!

1354
01:18:39,900 --> 01:18:42,400
All right, boys! Let's go! Let's go!

1355
01:18:42,400 --> 01:18:46,000
We're gonna need a bigger boat.
Stay here with the kids.

1356
01:18:55,100 --> 01:18:57,000
Come on, Rita!

1357
01:18:57,000 --> 01:19:01,200
Everyone, up the ramp! Onto the deck!
Come on! Hurry, hurry, hurry!

1358
01:19:01,300 --> 01:19:03,000
Dylan, get back inside! It's too dangerous.

1359
01:19:03,100 --> 01:19:05,100
No, Dad. I told you, I'm with you.

1360
01:19:09,500 --> 01:19:12,300
EVAN: Careful, everyone.
In the ark! In the ark!

1361
01:19:12,400 --> 01:19:14,500
Watch your step! Up the ramp, everybody!

1362
01:19:22,700 --> 01:19:23,800
Guys, help me with the door!

1363
01:19:23,900 --> 01:19:25,200
Get the door! Get the door!

1364
01:19:32,200 --> 01:19:34,100
(ALL SCREAMING)

1365
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,400
Guys! Guys!

1366
01:20:42,400 --> 01:20:44,100
Everybody hang on!

1367
01:20:54,400 --> 01:20:55,500
(ROARING)

1368
01:20:55,600 --> 01:20:57,800
You guys all right? You okay?

1369
01:20:58,400 --> 01:20:59,900
MAN OVER TV:
There's been a flood at Prestige Crest

1370
01:21:00,000 --> 01:21:02,200
and you're seeing live images
of New York Noah's ark

1371
01:21:02,200 --> 01:21:05,500
caught in the storm surge
and heading towards Memorial Bridge!

1372
01:21:13,300 --> 01:21:14,300
WOMAN: We're going to crash!

1373
01:21:14,400 --> 01:21:15,900
MAN: Turn this thing around!

1374
01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:17,300
MAN 2: We're not gonna make it!

1375
01:21:17,400 --> 01:21:18,800
MAN 3: Save us, Baxter!

1376
01:21:30,500 --> 01:21:35,100
I command thee halt! Stop! Whoa!

1377
01:21:35,200 --> 01:21:36,800
WOMAN: It's not working!

1378
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:40,400
How about a little help here?

1379
01:21:56,700 --> 01:21:57,700
(SCREAMING)

1380
01:22:24,800 --> 01:22:25,800
(SCREAMING)

1381
01:22:26,200 --> 01:22:28,700
What do you mean there was water damage?
It rained for ten minutes.

1382
01:22:28,800 --> 01:22:30,300
That is not possible.

1383
01:22:39,100 --> 01:22:40,200
(EXCLAIMING)

1384
01:22:40,200 --> 01:22:42,100
I love you guys.
All right.

1385
01:22:42,200 --> 01:22:43,500
Seriously.
Okay, I got it.

1386
01:22:43,500 --> 01:22:44,700
I love you.
Thank you.

1387
01:22:44,700 --> 01:22:46,000
(EAGLE CRYING)

1388
01:23:02,100 --> 01:23:06,700
LONG: All those in favor of the Public Land
Act, please signify by saying, "Aye."

1389
01:23:07,100 --> 01:23:09,000
(CLAMORING)

1390
01:23:13,800 --> 01:23:15,100
Good God!

1391
01:23:24,100 --> 01:23:25,900
(ALL YELLING)

1392
01:23:50,400 --> 01:23:51,900
I think we can walk from here.

1393
01:23:52,300 --> 01:23:53,500
(SIRENS BLARING)

1394
01:24:10,100 --> 01:24:14,700
Hello, Congressman.
Mind if I park my boat here for a little while?

1395
01:24:15,600 --> 01:24:16,600
But how...

1396
01:24:16,700 --> 01:24:17,900
The dam, Congressman.

1397
01:24:18,000 --> 01:24:21,600
Your reservoir ruptured.
Prestige Crest, it's all gone.

1398
01:24:21,600 --> 01:24:23,600
No. They said that couldn't happen.

1399
01:24:25,200 --> 01:24:26,600
I never thought this...

1400
01:24:27,800 --> 01:24:32,700
You. You did this to me.
You set me up, you crazy son of a...

1401
01:24:32,800 --> 01:24:35,900
(MONKEYS SCREECHING)

1402
01:24:36,000 --> 01:24:38,300
Wow. That is disgusting.

1403
01:24:38,800 --> 01:24:40,200
If that comes out your front,

1404
01:24:40,300 --> 01:24:42,600
I don't even want to know
what's coming out the back.

1405
01:24:45,500 --> 01:24:46,900
(SNARLING)

1406
01:24:47,000 --> 01:24:49,500
Don't look down, Congressman,
but the wolves are here,

1407
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:53,500
although I wouldn't worry so much
about these wolves as those.

1408
01:25:01,800 --> 01:25:03,200
Gesundheit.

1409
01:25:15,300 --> 01:25:18,900
MAN 1: As you can see behind me,
New York Noah's prediction came true.

1410
01:25:19,000 --> 01:25:21,500
WOMAN: The vote of the Land Act Bill
has been suspended,

1411
01:25:21,600 --> 01:25:24,400
pending investigation of Congressman Long
for profiteering...

1412
01:25:24,500 --> 01:25:27,500
MAN 2: Of course now, the question is,
how will these animals be returned

1413
01:25:27,500 --> 01:25:29,100
to their natural habitats?

1414
01:25:29,200 --> 01:25:33,000
Something tells me, if God got them here,
he can probably get them home.

1415
01:25:33,100 --> 01:25:36,200
WOMAN 2: The House will undoubtedly
reinstate Congressman Baxter

1416
01:25:36,200 --> 01:25:38,000
when it reconvenes in the morning.

1417
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:42,000
Until then, there is a lot to be done
here on Capitol Hill.

1418
01:25:42,000 --> 01:25:43,000
JORDAN: How's Buster doing?

1419
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:44,100
EVAN: Come on, Buster.

1420
01:25:44,200 --> 01:25:46,600
JOAN: No, come on. Come on!
RYAN: Come on!

1421
01:25:46,700 --> 01:25:48,500
EVAN: These too heavy? It's all right?
JORDAN: No, it's fine.

1422
01:25:48,500 --> 01:25:49,600
RYAN: He can't keep up.

1423
01:25:49,700 --> 01:25:51,000
I know, sweetie!

1424
01:25:51,000 --> 01:25:54,200
All right. What do you say
we take a little break?

1425
01:25:54,300 --> 01:25:55,900
We've only been walking
for, like, five minutes, Dad.

1426
01:25:56,000 --> 01:25:59,200
Well, five on, five off.
Life is about balance, right?

1427
01:25:59,300 --> 01:26:00,600
How about some sandwiches?
Okay.

1428
01:26:00,700 --> 01:26:02,300
Who wants sandwiches? Let's do it!

1429
01:26:02,400 --> 01:26:03,600
RYAN: I get first dibs!

1430
01:26:03,600 --> 01:26:06,000
Everyone but Buster
is going to get a sandwich.

1431
01:26:06,000 --> 01:26:10,400
You do not get a sandwich! You're a dog
and you do not get a sandwich!

1432
01:26:10,500 --> 01:26:13,700
Buster is part of the family now.
You're just gonna have to get used to it.

1433
01:26:13,800 --> 01:26:15,600
Poor Buster!

1434
01:26:16,400 --> 01:26:19,500
Honey, come here.
Sweetheart, be careful. Come here.

1435
01:26:19,600 --> 01:26:21,500
Hey, hon, save me one, okay?
Okay.

1436
01:26:21,500 --> 01:26:22,700
I'll be right back.

1437
01:26:31,300 --> 01:26:32,700
Hey.
Hey.

1438
01:26:34,500 --> 01:26:36,000
What are you doing here?

1439
01:26:36,800 --> 01:26:39,200
Just hanging out with some old friends.

1440
01:26:39,300 --> 01:26:42,600
You knew all along, didn't you?
You knew the dam was unstable.

1441
01:26:42,700 --> 01:26:46,500
If it hadn't been for the ark,
my family, the neighbors...

1442
01:26:46,600 --> 01:26:48,800
I fought you every step of the way.

1443
01:26:48,900 --> 01:26:50,400
Yes, but you did it.

1444
01:26:51,400 --> 01:26:56,000
So, you had nothing to do with the flood?
Like where the ark landed exactly?

1445
01:26:56,000 --> 01:26:59,500
I gave you a little shove at the end. Sue me.

1446
01:26:59,600 --> 01:27:00,600
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

1447
01:27:02,100 --> 01:27:05,800
You did good, son. You changed the world.

1448
01:27:05,900 --> 01:27:07,300
No, no, I didn't.

1449
01:27:07,400 --> 01:27:08,600
Well, let's see.

1450
01:27:08,600 --> 01:27:12,700
Spending time with your family,
making them very happy.

1451
01:27:12,800 --> 01:27:14,100
Gave that dog a home.

1452
01:27:14,200 --> 01:27:16,100
Right. So?

1453
01:27:16,800 --> 01:27:18,500
So?

1454
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:20,700
How do we change the world?

1455
01:27:22,200 --> 01:27:25,700
One act of random kindness at a time.

1456
01:27:25,700 --> 01:27:30,300
One act of random kindness.

1457
01:27:30,400 --> 01:27:31,500
EVAN: Wow.

1458
01:27:35,500 --> 01:27:36,800
It's time.

1459
01:27:38,800 --> 01:27:40,300
Do the dance.

1460
01:27:41,800 --> 01:27:43,400
Care to join me?

1461
01:27:49,300 --> 01:27:50,300
(CHUCKLING)

1462
01:28:05,400 --> 01:28:06,400
(DOVE COOING)

1463
01:28:39,900 --> 01:28:42,700
I now issue a new commandment,

1464
01:28:42,700 --> 01:28:44,800
"Thou shalt do the dance."

1465
01:28:44,900 --> 01:28:46,600
(GONNA MAKE YOU SWEAT,
EVERYBODY DANCE NOW PLAYING)

1466
01:29:40,700 --> 01:29:42,200
(LIP-SYNCING)

1467
01:29:46,900 --> 01:29:50,100
Stop it! This is stupid!

1468
01:29:50,200 --> 01:29:53,400
That's awful dancing! You better stop!

1469
01:29:59,200 --> 01:30:18,000
(LIP-SYNCING)

1470
01:30:26,300 --> 01:30:28,000
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

1471
01:30:31,700 --> 01:30:33,800
MAN 1: Ladies and gentlemen,
you don't have to go home.

1472
01:30:33,900 --> 01:30:36,500
You just have to go. We are wrapped.

1473
01:30:36,600 --> 01:30:39,300
MAN 2: We're wrapped.
We love you. Thank you.

1474
01:30:40,100 --> 01:30:42,100
(READY FOR A MIRACLE PLAYING)

